1349","1359":"1359","1435":"1435","1347":"1347","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","about 1375":"omkring 1375","1417":"1417","Belper, Derbyshire, England":"Belper, Derbyshire, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1349–1389":"1349–1389","1347–1399":"1347–1399","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1 February 1359":"1 februari 1359","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1359":"1359","1435":"1435","1347":"1347","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","about 1375":"circa 1375","1417":"1417","Belper, Derbyshire, England":"Belper, Derbyshire, England","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1349–1389":"1349–1389","1347–1399":"1347–1399","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1 February 1359":"1 February 1359","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1359":"1359","1435":"1435","1347":"1347","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","about 1375":"about 1375","1417":"1417","Belper, Derbyshire, England":"Belper, Derbyshire, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Harley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from either of two places called Harley (Shropshire, Yorkshire). The Shropshire placename derives from Old English <i>hær</i> ‘rock, heap of stones’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. The Yorkshire placename derives from Old English <i>hara</i> ‘hare’ or <i>hær</i> + <i>hlāw</i> ‘mound, hill’, later replaced by <i>lēah</i>.","Irish (Donegal): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEarghaile</b> ‘descendant of <i>Earghal</i>’, a variant of the personal name <i>Fearghal</i> without the initial <i>F-</i>. This name has also become   Herley   and   Hurley  . Compare   Arrell   and   Harrell  .","Scottish (Fife): habitational name from any of several places called Harlaw in Midlothian, Peeblesshire, and Berwickshire, named in Older Scots with <i>hare</i> ‘gray’ + <i>law</i> ‘hill’."],"variants":[{"name":"Herley","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Art, Cormac.","Irish: variant of   Hurley  , probably via   Herlihy  .","English: variant of   Harley   or   Hurley  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":33,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Harley was born in 1349, in Little Brampton, Shropshire, England, her father, Robert De Harley, was 30 and her mother, Joan Corbet, was 18. She married John Hammond about 1375, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1389, in Herefordshire, England, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1349–1389":"1349–1389","1347–1399":"1347–1399","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1 February 1359":"1. veebruar 1359","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1359":"1359","1435":"1435","1347":"1347","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","about 1375":"umbes 1375","1417":"1417","Belper, Derbyshire, England":"Belper, Derbyshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1349–1389":"1349–1389","1347–1399":"1347–1399","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1320–1359":"1320–1359","1332–1417":"1332–1417","1 February 1359":"1. helmikuuta 1359","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1359":"1359","1435":"1435","1347":"1347","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","about 1375":"noin 1375","1417":"1417","Belper, Derbyshire, England":"Belper, Derbyshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","Little Brampton, Shropshire, England":"Little Brampton, Shropshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Sh